    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe async fn are not yet supported?</p>",
        "id": 577259773,
        "sender_full_name": "Ludea",
        "timestamp": 1772640765
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You need to look up the <code>myinterface</code> export first, then get the <code>myfunction</code> export from that.  Let me see if I can find an example.</p>",
        "id": 577260567,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Dice",
        "timestamp": 1772640964
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's a example (although it doesn't involve an async-typed function): <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/8adf03d4557acaa8384ec084946614d3f87c39ff/tests/all/component_model/func.rs#L3645-L3650\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/8adf03d4557acaa8384ec084946614d3f87c39ff/tests/all/component_model/func.rs#L3645-L3650</a></p>",
        "id": 577261597,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Dice",
        "timestamp": 1772641224
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks will try when go back to office</p>",
        "id": 577263733,
        "sender_full_name": "Ludea",
        "timestamp": 1772641769
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>get_exports_name</code> name arg is instance name?</p>",
        "id": 577521130,
        "sender_full_name": "Ludea",
        "timestamp": 1772722556
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instance_index</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instance</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_export_index</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">store</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"i\"</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">//here</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 577521396,
        "sender_full_name": "Ludea",
        "timestamp": 1772722610
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The last parameter to <code>get_export_index</code> is the exported instance name, yes.  In the example I linked to, see the WAT component being used, which exports an instance named <code>i</code> which exports a function named <code>new</code> and a type named <code>r</code>.</p>",
        "id": 577546569,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Dice",
        "timestamp": 1772728315
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How to get instance name?<br>\nI don't use wat component, so I instanciate through wasmtime and linker</p>",
        "id": 577563366,
        "sender_full_name": "Ludea",
        "timestamp": 1772732793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If I use <code>myinterface</code> as instance naming, instance is not found</p>",
        "id": 577571629,
        "sender_full_name": "Ludea",
        "timestamp": 1772735448
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In the case of the WIT you posted above, I'd expect the instance name to be <code>mycomponent:remote/myinterface@0.1.0</code>.  You can check for sure using e.g. <code>wasm-tools print $your_wasm_file</code> and looking at the exports near the bottom of the output.</p>",
        "id": 577578189,
        "sender_full_name": "Joel Dice",
        "timestamp": 1772737650
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Awesome it works as expected.<br>\nThanks for the help !<br>\nI get another issue :</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">thread</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">tokio</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">runtime</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">worker</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">14529</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">panicked</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">src</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">plugins</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">74</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">62</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"nc\">called</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">on</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">an</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">while</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">executing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wasm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">backtrace</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mh\">0x